label("$(\sqrt{3},0)$", B, NE);
label("$(\frac{\sqrt{6}}{2}, -\frac{\sqrt{6}}{2})$", C, C);
[/asy]

The triangle has base $\sqrt{6}$ and height $\sqrt{3} - \frac{\sqrt{6}}{2},$ so its area is
\[\frac{1}{2} \cdot \sqrt{6} \cdot \left( \sqrt{3} - \frac{\sqrt{6}}{2} \right) = \boxed{\frac{3 \sqrt{2} - 3}{2}}.\]

